    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🚀 Event Creation Workflow\n\nThis section handles **new events** created in Google Calendar.\n\n1.  **Event Created (Google Calendar Trigger)**: Initiates the workflow when a new event is detected.\n2.  **Get Google Event**: Fetches the full details of the newly created Google Calendar event.\n3.  **AI Agent1**: Decides whether to create a corresponding event in Outlook based on predefined rules, including searching for existing Outlook events to prevent duplicates.\n4.  **Edit Fields**: Processes the output of the AI Agent.\n5.  **If**: Checks the AI Agent's decision to determine if an Outlook event should be created.\n6.  **Create an event in Microsoft Outlook**: If no duplicate is found and creation is allowed, this node creates the event in Outlook.\n7.  **Update an event (Google Calendar)**: (Conditional) If an Outlook event is successfully created, this node updates the Google Calendar event to tag it with the Outlook Event ID, preventing future loops.",
        "height": 492,
        "width": 800
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        -32,
        -320
      ],
      "name": "Event Creation Logic",
      "id": "d860ae8e-edee-4cac-b6fe-7b03ee067388",
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔄 Event Update Workflow\n\nThis section manages **updates to existing events** in Google Calendar.\n\n1.  **Event Updated (Google Calendar Trigger)**: Triggers when an event is modified in Google Calendar.\n2.  **Get Google Event3**: Retrieves the latest details of the updated Google Calendar event.\n3.  **AI Agent4**: Determines if the corresponding Outlook event should be updated. It checks if the event was previously synced by AgentCal and searches for a matching Outlook event.\n4.  **Edit Fields1**: Processes the output of the AI Agent.\n5.  **If1**: Evaluates the AI Agent's decision to proceed with the Outlook event update.\n6.  **Update an event in Microsoft Outlook2**: If a match is found and an update is permitted, this node updates the specific Outlook event.\n7.  **Update an event1 (Google Calendar)**: (Conditional) Updates the Google Calendar event to reflect the sync status.",
        "height": 492,
        "width": 896,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "name": "Event Update Logic",
      "position": [
        -96,
        544
      ],
      "id": "9e720f7a-49c8-43c9-860b-71f6c30b7785",
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🗑️ Event Cancellation Workflow\n\nThis section handles **cancelled events** in Google Calendar.\n\n1.  **Event Cancelled (Google Calendar Trigger)**: Activates when an event is cancelled in Google Calendar.\n2.  **Get Google Event4**: Fetches the details of the cancelled Google Calendar event.\n3.  **AI Agent5**: Decides whether to delete the corresponding Outlook event. It verifies if the event was originally synced by AgentCal and attempts to find a precise match in Outlook.\n4.  **No direct deletion**: The AI Agent only makes a *decision*. The actual deletion of the Outlook event would typically be handled by subsequent nodes based on the AI Agent's `shouldDeleteOutlook` output, though those nodes are not currently present in this workflow branch. This ensures a safe, decision-based cancellation process.",
        "height": 468,
        "width": 848,
        "color": 3
      },
      "position": [
        -32,
        1136
      ],
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "name": "Event Cancellation Logic",
      "id": "a9c1a94b-ec96-4832-b3ec-af6f33a658f6",
      "typeVersion": 1
